text: Phaenomenella is a genus of sea snails, marine gastropod mollusks in the family Buccinidae, the true whelks. ==Species== According to the World Register of Marine Species (WoRMS), the following species with valid names are included within the genus Phaenomenella :WoRMS : Phaenomenella; accessed : 6 September 2010 * Phaenomenella angusta Hadorn & Fraussen, 2006 * Phaenomenella callophorella (Fraussen, 2003) * Phaenomenella cirsiumoides (Fraussen, 2004) * Phaenomenella inflata (Shikama, 1971) * Phaenomenella insulapratasensis (Okutani & Lan, 1994) * Phaenomenella mokenorum Fraussen, 2008 * Phaenomenella nicoi Kantor, Kosyan, Sorokin & Fedosov, 2020 * Phaenomenella samadiae Kantor, Kosyan, Sorokin & Fedosov, 2020Small text * Phaenomenella thachi Fraussen & Stahlschmidt, 2012 * Phaenomenella venusta Fraussen & Stahlschmidt, 2012 * Phaenomenella vexabilis Fraussen & Stahlschmidt, 2013 ==References== * Fraussen K. & Hadorn R. 2006. Phaenomenella, a new genus of deep-water buccinid (Gastropoda: Buccinidae) with the description of a new species from Taiwan. Novapex 7(4): 103-109. Category:Buccinidae
title: Phaenomenella
